      <body>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_TireeKMacDonaldslips-idp117238824">
            <form>
               <orth>rangais</orth>
               <pron>[rɑŋɡiʃ]</pron>
            </form>
            <def>[rɑŋɡiʃ] Notes: the strap running the length of the boat on which the seats rest on each side.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_TireeKMacDonaldslips-idp117240552">
            <form>
               <orth>reang</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quotation: reangan stòbhaig [rɛ̃ɣəṉsṯɔ:viɡʹ]. Notes: ribs put between the “urlair”. Laid across the boat, steamed and stood on.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_TireeKMacDonaldslips-idp117242424">
            <form>
               <orth>cailleach-bhàn</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Notes: a cod with parasites on it.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_TireeKMacDonaldslips-idp117243936">
            <form>
               <orth>cròdach</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quotation: a’ chròdach. Notes: animal rheumatism – sheep, cattle.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_TireeKMacDonaldslips-idp117245592">
            <form>
               <orth>doire</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quotation: doire an eathar. Notes: the hull of the boat.</def>
         </entry>
         <entry xml:id="Slips_TireeKMacDonaldslips-idp117247248">
            <form>
               <orth>dòrn</orth>
            </form>
            <def>Quotation: a’ toirt a mach an dòrn fhuar. Notes: feat of strength tried when a cow was killed. One of the legs was caught near the hoof and twisted till it broke from the knee, then twisting was continued till the skin broke.</def>
         </entry>
